---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Terms of Service — Parry"
  description="Parry's terms of service. Read about the rules and guidelines for using the Parry app."
  canonicalPath="/terms"
>
  <section class="px-5 py-16 md:px-8 md:py-20">
    <div class="prose-legal mx-auto max-w-3xl">
      <h1 class="mb-2 font-[var(--font-sora)] text-3xl font-bold md:text-4xl">Terms of Service</h1>
      <p class="mb-8 text-sm text-text-tertiary">Last updated: February 2026</p>

      <h2>1. Acceptance of Terms</h2>
      <p>
        By downloading, installing, or using Parry ("the App"), you agree to be bound by these Terms of Service.
      </p>

      <h2>2. Description of Service</h2>
      <p>
        Parry is an AI-powered mobile application that generates text message response suggestions. The app uses artificial intelligence to analyze input text and provide response options.
      </p>

      <h2>3. Use of the Service</h2>
      <p>You agree to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Use the app only for lawful purposes</li>
        <li>Not use the app to harass, abuse, or harm others</li>
        <li>Not attempt to circumvent security features</li>
        <li>Not use the app to generate illegal, harmful, or inappropriate content</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>4. AI-Generated Content</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Responses are generated by AI and may not always be appropriate</li>
        <li>You are responsible for reviewing and editing responses before sending</li>
        <li>We do not guarantee the accuracy or appropriateness of AI-generated content</li>
        <li>You should not rely on AI suggestions for critical communications</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>5. Subscriptions and Payments</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Free tier: Limited to 3 generations per day</li>
        <li>Pro subscription: Unlimited generations and additional features</li>
        <li>Subscriptions are billed through Apple App Store or Google Play</li>
        <li>Subscription terms are governed by the respective app store</li>
        <li>Refunds are handled by the app store according to their policies</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>6. Cancellation</h2>
      <p>You may cancel your subscription at any time through:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>iOS:</strong> Settings &gt; [Your Name] &gt; Subscriptions</li>
        <li><strong>Android:</strong> Play Store &gt; Subscriptions</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Cancellation takes effect at the end of the current billing period.</p>

      <h2>7. Intellectual Property</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>The app and its content are owned by Parry</li>
        <li>AI-generated responses are provided for your personal use</li>
        <li>You may not resell or redistribute the app or its outputs</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>8. Disclaimer of Warranties</h2>
      <p>
        The app is provided "as is" without warranties of any kind. We do not guarantee that:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>The app will be error-free or uninterrupted</li>
        <li>AI responses will be appropriate for all situations</li>
        <li>The app will meet your specific requirements</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>9. Limitation of Liability</h2>
      <p>
        To the maximum extent permitted by law, we shall not be liable for any indirect, incidental, special, or consequential damages arising from your use of the app.
      </p>

      <h2>10. Changes to Terms</h2>
      <p>
        We may modify these terms at any time. Continued use of the app after changes constitutes acceptance of the new terms.
      </p>

      <h2>11. Governing Law</h2>
      <p>
        These terms are governed by the laws of Washington, United States.
      </p>

      <h2>12. Contact</h2>
      <p>
        For questions about these Terms, contact:<br />
        Email: <a href="mailto:support@parryai.app">support@parryai.app</a>
      </p>

      <p class="mt-8 text-sm text-text-tertiary">&copy; 2026 Parry. All rights reserved.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
